text: By the time I made it about 45 seconds into the movie, I knew some kind of serious morons were involved, super serious morons. For those wondering HOW serious, these are the kind of morons who can't even use a calculator.....  2400 times a year, 44 times a week, 9 times a day, every 48 minutes....blah blah blah. Any competent 3rd grader should easily recognize the fact that "every 48 minutes" would be far more than 9x a day, and I only point that out in particular since it's the easiest to see being wrong...  2400 / 52 = 46.15 times a week = 6.6 times a day = 218 minutes......honestly it might be nitpicking, but FML if you've got your movie opening with something so obviously retarded then what the hell do you want from us? I realize maybe they expect average movie-goers to have sub-par intelligence, but this is just insulting.....

text: This movie is basically an homage to Heat, right down to the running gun fight in traffic, vs just being a remake per se. Tough cop and tough bank robber with a tough crew go head to head. They attempt to give us some reason to care about characters with the usual fare (tough cop getting divorced and misses his kids, drinks too much, yada, yada) and is generally well done with a solid cast, with a few eye rolling moments that knock down what could have been a really good movie. I expected 50 cent to be terrible, but he actually does a decent job of it.  Dialogue is ok, some scenes are tense and taught, and it's an overall fun action movie, but Heat or Sicario it aint... But it's not a bad action flick, just not one you'll be talking about the next day or thinking about past seeing it. B-
